args: We've gotta finish the rest of these\nweapon orders today!
Ramona, can we maybe have one day\nwhere we DON'T go through this?
Wait, are you okay? You look terrible.
Oh man, you have a serious fever.\nI bet you caught a cold.
Right then. Stay in bed, you two.
I'll make you something to get your\nstrength up and find clothes that\naren't covered in sweat and ick!
...Okay, that's sorted. Don't worry,\nI'll be by your side until you get—
Wait, I don't have TIME to be at your side!\nI gotta finish these weapons!
But if I'm the only one able to work...\nOh man, this is baaaaad.
We've never been in so much trouble!
Well, there's only one thing to do...\nI'm gonna make the weapons myself!
If we don't make this deadline,\nno one will ever trust us again!
Okay, Renee, you can do this...\nYou can SO do this!
Everyone says you're a genius when it\ncomes to smithing, so it's gonna be fine!
I'll put all my knowledge into this!\nAll my experience! All my dreams!\nAll of it...into...thiiiiiis! Raaaah!
Hee hee! All I did was try to mimic\nwhatever my sisters do, but I think\nI actually pulled it off!
Yes, it seems you have quite the eye\nfor this sort of thing.
Hee hee! Heya, Malka! So ummm...\nyou can keep praising me if you want.
Yes, this is indeed spectacular work.\n...On the surface.
Swing it. You'll see what I mean.
Oh, I'll swing it, all right—I'll swing it\nright in your smug face! HYARRRRGH!
Oh man, this thing is SUPER wonky.\nIt won't even swing right.
Do you see now? The center of gravity is\ncompletely misplaced; it would be a\ndeath sentence to wield this in battle.
There's no need for such disappointment;\nthis is stellar work for one of your age.
You were able to perfectly replicate the\nappearance of your sisters' weapons.\nGiven enough time, you might—
I don't HAVE time! If this isn't done now,\nthe entire smithy goes under!
Which is why I am here.
I will give you all the advice you need to\ncraft weapons suitable for your clients.
Seriously?! Oh, thank you! With your help,\nI know I can finish the remaining ten!
You have an order of TEN?! Oh dear.\nI think we're going to need more hands\nto accomplish that task.
Then what are we gonna dooo?
Yep! Aoi the ninja, at your service—\nwhether you like it or not.
I heard you were in trouble,\nso I've come to lend a hand.
I will also help in whatever way I can.
Aw, I can't believe you all came!
I really need the help, so thank you.
But the smithy is too dangerous for kids,\nso while I REALLY appreciate the offer,\nyou two will have to stand back.
You want us to watch? Booo-ring!
Yeah! We could really use a cheer squad!
Take up that hammer, Renee!\nThe day grows short!
Leave the furnace to me and my\nfiery ninja techniques. ...Haaah!
Thanks, Aoi! Now I can concentrate\non swinging this thing!
You must swing it like THIS, Renee.\nRemember it well!
Here's a bucket with clean water!
Go, Renee, go! Go, Renee, go!
Eventually, after much hard work from everyone...
Well done! We have ten flawless weapons\nfit for the most demanding of customers!
Yaaay, we did it!\nAnd oof, I'm sooo tired...
Well done, Renee. Thanks to you,\nthe crisis has been averted.
Hee hee! As long as I'm still standing\nthere's nothing to fear.
...Er, or so I'd like to say,\nbut I actually had a ton of help.
I can't call myself the best blacksmith\naround if I need all of you to bail me out.
But you looked so cool when you\nwere forging stuff!
Yeah, we all saw how hard you worked!

The kids are right—there's no need to be
hard on yourself. You pursued your dream
with fierce determination, and I personally
think you killed it.
Now you just have to make that dream\na permanent reality.
And if you ever feel like you need to cry,\nI'll be there to comfort you.
Me too! We'll always be at your back!
You're treating me like a kid again!
I think that is one of your best qualities.
What, my ability to have kids younger\nthan me treat me like I'M the child?
When you think about it, it just means\nyou're loved by your elders AND juniors.
I still get the feeling you're not\nACTUALLY complimenting me.
Ha ha! Listen, every artisan has their\nown strengths and style.

Your ability to be loved by everyone you
meet is a key part of yours—and what
makes you the artisan you are. It is
something that's uniquely Renee.
So you're saying that the ability to make\neveryone gather together like this\nis one of my strengths?
...Hey, yeah! That IS a talent! I mean,\nwe barely know each other, but you\nall came rushing to my aid.
So if I keep trying lots of new things\nand meeting tons of new people...
Wooo! Okay, now I am SUPER motivated!\nI'm going to become the best blacksmith\never, and I'll do it MY way!
Well said! Just remember that everyone\nhere is also rooting for your success.
With everyone's help and support,\nI'll keep cranking out great weapons.
That's the kind of blacksmith I'll be—\nthe one that ONLY I can be!
